==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: one-way
<hw>one-way</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Legally permitting
movement or travel in one direction only; -- of paths, especially roads;
<as>as, <ex>one-way</ex> streets</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Transportation)</fld> <def>Pertaining to or valid
for transportation in one direction between two points; <as>as, a
<ex>one-way</ex> ticket; a <ex>one-way</ex> fare</as>. Opposed to
<ant>round-trip</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>one-woman</ent>⟦br⟧
